What is a Text Widget?
Simple definition: A widget that displays text on the screen. It's the most basic way to show words in your app.

Think of it like: An <h1>, <p>, or <span> tag in HTML.

The 5 Most Important Properties


1️⃣ data (The Text to Display)
What it does: The actual text string to show.

dart
Text('Hello World')





2️⃣ style (How It Looks)
What it does: Controls font size, color, weight, etc.

dart
Text(
  'Hello World',
  style: TextStyle(
    fontSize: 24,
    color: Colors.blue,
    fontWeight: FontWeight.bold,
  ),
)




3️⃣ textAlign (Horizontal Alignment)
What it does: Aligns text left, center, or right.

dart
Text(
  'Hello World',
  textAlign: TextAlign.center,  // left, center, right, justify
)







4️⃣ overflow (What to Do When Too Long)
What it does: Controls how overflowing text is handled.

Value	What It Does
TextOverflow.ellipsis	           Adds ... at the end
TextOverflow.clip	               Cuts off the text
TextOverflow.fade	               Fades out at the end
TextOverflow.visible	           Shows overflowing text

dart
Text(
  'This is a very long text that will overflow',
  overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis,  // Adds "..."
  maxLines: 1,
)




5️⃣ maxLines (How Many Lines)
What it does: Limits the number of lines displayed.

dart
Text(
  'This is a long text that will wrap to multiple lines',
  maxLines: 2,  // Only shows 2 lines
  overflow: TextOverflow.ellipsis,
)



